---
title: Plant-Based Protein Messy Janes with Pickled Onion, Roasted Potato Wedges & Lime Mayo
description: Craving the ultimate throwback of the humble sloppy joe—minus the meat? Look no further. This version stars ground, plant-based protein, and is worlds tastier than the ones the lunch lady slung: Think pickled onion, a smoky BBQ sauce, and a side of hearty potato wedges. (We’d still highly recommend keeping a few napkins nearby, though.)
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/633c68533710fc579f0a6961-c381d827.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/plant-based-protein-messy-janes-633c68533710fc579f0a6961-39993da3.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/plant-based-protein-messy-janes-633c68533710fc579f0a6961
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 121 g
  sugar: 38 g
  protein: 23 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 1990 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a
large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}(reserving 1 tsp for later),
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until lightly browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, halve, peel, and very thinly slice ¼ of the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and very thinly sliced);
finely chop remaining. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve @brioche buns{2}.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, juice from half the lime,
@sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of salt. Microwave until onion is softened, ~{1%minute}.
Set aside.

In a #second small bowl{}, combine @BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{2%tablespoon},
@Mushroom stock concentrate{1}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}(reserving half for later),
remaining Southwest spice blend, and @water{1%tablespoon}.

In a #third small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} and a squeeze of lime
juice. Season with salt.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chopped onion;
cook, stirring, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @ground plant-based protein{6%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Using a
spatula, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up protein into pieces and continue cooking until browned and warmed through,
~{3-4%minutes} more.

Add @water{2%tablespoon} to pan with plant-based protein, then stir in BBQ sauce
mixture. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season
with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, toast buns until golden brown.

Divide buns between plates; spread cut sides of bottom buns with lime mayo. Fill
buns with messy jane filling and as much pickled onion (draining first) as you
like. Serve with potato wedges on the side and any remaining lime mayo for dipping.

> Ground Plant-Based Protein is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.